bibdata.title: Keying off of retention codes for the barcode endpoint used for SCSB accession

comments.body:
https://github.com/pulibrary/bibdata/blob/main/app/controllers/barcode_controller.rb#L14

Location that "Shared" is in now...
https://github.com/pulibrary/bibdata/blob/a26c5d30aefa2ef3f19ad499bb3bae4348f0e7c2/app/adapters/alma_adapter/alma_item.rb#L178

The desired end result is that:

1. The SCSB goes to https://bibdata.princeton.edu/barcode/[BARCODE_OF_SCSB_ITEM]/scsb
2. If the alma endpoint @mzelesky documented has `"committed_to_retain": { "value": "true", "desc": "Yes" }`, bibdata will return a MARC record that includes an 876$xCommitted, rather than 876$xShared.
3. If the alma endpoint doesn't have this `committed_to_retain` info, then keep the current behavior.

See https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1kn4ixrZcvjdP3UPG1zL2ytfFO16OUN77ZWyT9ous9hM/edit?usp=sharing for an analysis of the frequency of each ICPSR heading.

Some cleanup of the MARC records should happen alongside this effort, to make the $2 values consistent (the official value is `icpsr` in lowercase). Also, some errant $0 values are in the data (LCSH URIs even though they are ICPSR headings).
Mark estimates the clean-up work is an hour or two.

figgy.title: Rake task to sync all pulfalight resources
Generate report for any and all Cotsen Items within the Digital Repository

comments.body:
Hello!

Cotsen Children's Library is grappling with one issue. We don't know what titles have been digitized, in full or only partially, from our collection. This happened since PUL adopted decentralized digitization practices and uploaded images from patron requests to Figgy as well. We would like to curate a DPUL collection <https://dpul.princeton.edu/cotsen> that contains all _complete_ digital surrogates of Cotsen's holdings.

I hope this explains the context of the request for report? We sorely need a good help with clearing up errors we keep spotting in DPUL concerning the organization of Cotsen titles. Keyword searching proves not reliable/exhaustive. Please let me know any further clarification we can provide. Thanks!

Minjie
